{"title":"How to make a PDF on iPhone","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/673649/how-to-create-a-pdf-on-iphone.html","date":1710191984000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>You can turn any type of document into a PDF on iPhone in seconds, and since the functionality is built into the Share option you don’t need third-party apps to get started. Here’s how to convert to PDF on iPhone or iPad.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For most documents (web pages and more) you can chose the Markup option:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Tap the <em>Share</em> button.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose <em>Markup</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You can draw or write on the PDF, or just tap <em>Done</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose <em>Save File To…</em> and select the location and filename for your PDF.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"create pdf iphone web page\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 4733w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=1200%2C800&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=1536%2C1024&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=2048%2C1366&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=1240%2C826&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1240w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/web-create-pdf-iphone.jpg?resize=150%2C100&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 150w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" loading=\"lazy\" /></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Some file types, like images, don’t give you the Markup option. For those, you can use the print preview to create and save a PDF:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Open the document or image file and tap the <em>Share</em> button.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Choose <em>Print</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>You’ll see an interface to select your printer and number of copies, with a preview at the bottom. Long-press on the preview.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The preview will pop up on your screen. Tap it to select it and a PDF will be created.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use the <em>Share</em> button on the lower left of the PDF preview to copy, save as a file, or send it to someone.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"iPhone image create PDF\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 5481w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=1200%2C800&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=1536%2C1024&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=2048%2C1365&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=1240%2C826&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1240w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/iphone-image-create-pdf.jpg?resize=150%2C100&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 150w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" loading=\"lazy\" /></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also be interested in: <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/232686/how-to-scan-documents-and-make-pdfs-on-your-iphone-or-ipad.html\">How to scan documents on iPhone or iPad</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/672595/how-to-edit-a-pdf-on-mac.html\">How To Edit A PDF On Mac</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/668866/best-free-pdf-editors-for-mac.html\">Best Free PDF Editor For Mac</a>.</p>\n\niOS, iPhone, PDF Editors</div>","author":"","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"044f4624c19f289896c47becf56bfdb2c7e18a2bfe093880aac21290670fc4a7","category":"Apple"}